cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper involves computer vision (CV) techniques for action recognition, as well as graphics (GR) techniques for generating synthetic videos using game engines. The paper also introduces a deep learning architecture for representation learning (LG) and uses probabilistic graphical models (AI) for the generative model. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (MM) data, specifically videos. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
